ars ago I finally got around to looking back into the box of personal field journals I had not opened for over forty years. I found a treasure trove. It was an overwhelming experience. So much that I had forgotten came vividly alive: I laughed, wept, and was terrified all over again at my temerity in taking on what I had taken on. To do justice to the richness of these notebooks, I realized, I would have to do a completely different sort of writing from anything I had ever done before.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Social Scientists & Psychologists.2bisacsh2 aKnowledge Unlatchedefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781805390664?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781805390664zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781805390664/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA